dct_title_s: [Indiana Vocational Technical College regional divisions map]
dct_description_sm: Title derived by cataloger from accompanying text. Shows administrative regions adopted by the Indiana Vocational Technical College (IVTC), including those with established regional institutes and those offering courses by 1968. "At the suggestion of the legislature, IVTC has divided the state into 13 regions, each of which will eventually have regional steering committees, 7-member boards of trustees, a paid regional director and such staff as necessary"--Accompanying text. Appears in Indiana almanac and fact book. Second annual edition, 1968-1969. Indianapolis : Ed Leary & Associates, 1969. Page 163.
Dimensions: 2 v. ill. 22 cm.; Scale: Scale not given.
